text: Nocardiopsis fildesensis is a bacterium from the genus of Nocardiopsis which has been isolated from soil from the Chinese Antarctic Great Wall Station on the King George Island.UniProt == References == ==External links== *Type strain of Nocardiopsis fildesensis at BacDive - the Bacterial Diversity Metadatabase Category:Actinomycetales Category:Bacteria described in 2014
title: Nocardiopsis fildesensis
